# Astro Guidelines

## Project Structure
- Follow Astro's recommended project structure
- Use src/pages/ for routing
- Place components in src/components/
- Store static assets in public/
- Use src/utils/ for utility functions
- Organize content in src/content/ (if using collections)

## Component Architecture
- Use islands architecture for interactive components
- Implement partial hydration effectively
- Use framework components (React, Vue, Svelte) when needed
- Leverage Astro's component syntax
- Follow best practices for component composition

## Static Site Generation (SSG)
- Implement efficient static generation
- Use Astro's zero-JS-by-default approach
- Optimize for Core Web Vitals
- Implement proper build optimization
- Leverage Astro's performance features

## Content Collections
- Use content collections for structured content
- Implement proper content modeling
- Use MDX for rich content when needed
- Implement content validation
- Follow best practices for content management

## Integration Patterns
- Use integrations for additional functionality
- Integrate with CMS platforms appropriately
- Implement proper API routes when necessary
- Use middleware for request processing
- Follow integration best practices

